} The Punisher 2017-2019 A rocky start can't keep The Punisher from pushing the boundaries of Marvel's TV universe with a fresh take on the comics-derived action thriller. Daredevil 2015-2018 With tight adherence to its source material's history, high production quality, and a no-nonsense dramatic flair, Daredevil excels as an effective superhero origin story, a gritty procedural, and an exciting action adventure. Gotham 2014-2019 High production values, a talented cast, and an appealingly stylized approach to the Batman mythos help Gotham overcome its occasionally familiar themes. {/*Second row of cards */} Jessica Jones 2015-2019 Jessica Jones builds a multifaceted drama around its engaging antihero, delivering what might be Marvel's strongest TV franchise to date. Vikings 2013-Present Vikings makes up for its lack of historical accuracy with a heaping helping of violence, romance, and striking visuals. Prison Break 2005-2017 Prison Break is confident pulp with a crackerjack premise that spreads thinly enough to smooth over the show's more lunkheaded flourishes. {/*Third row of cards */} True Detective 2014-Present In True Detective, performances by Woody Harrelsen and Matthew McConaughey reel the viewer in, while the style, vision and direction make it hard to turn away. Mindhunter 2017-Present Mindhunter distinguishes itself in a crowded genre with ambitiously cinematic visuals and a meticulous attention to character development. House of Cards 2013-2018 Bolstered by strong performances -- especially from Kevin Spacey -- and surehanded direction, House of Cards is a slick, engrossing drama that may redefine how television is produced. {/*Fourth row of three card images on the page*/} The Sopranos 1999-2007 The Sopranos smartly runs an emotional gamut, offering detailed character work and riveting suspense while displaying a flair for both comedy and drama. The Wire 2002-2008 Though it takes its time getting started, The Wire is worth the wait, spinning a connective web of characters and delivering no-holds-barred commentary on some of America's unsettling societal problems. Mad Men 2007-2015 Oozing evocative early 1960s ambiance, Mad Men is a sly, subversive look at the American workplace that radiates class, wit, and an undercurrent of disaffection. {/*Fifth row of cards */} Brooklyn Nine Nine 2013-Present Led by the surprisingly effective pairing of Andy Samberg and Andre Braugher, Brooklyn Nine-Nine is a charming, intelligently written take on the cop show format. It's Always Sunny In Philadelphia 2005-Present t's Always Sunny's winning formula keeps the laughs rolling and the stomachs turning in a thirteenth season that's topical, triumphant, and toxic in the best way. Silicon Valley 2014-Present Silicon Valley is a relevant, often hilarious take on contemporary technology and the geeks who create it that benefits from co-creator Mike Judge's real-life experience in the industry {/*Sixth row of cards*/} Arrested Development 2003-Present Arrested Development puts an ambitiously complex, brilliantly fast-paced spin on dysfunctional family comedy, anchored by the efforts of a tremendously talented ensemble. Curb Your Enthusiasm 2000-Present Playing an exaggerated version of himself, Larry David proves that his comic genius is at full force both behind and in front of the camera. South Park 1997-Present South Park deploys blisteringly insightful gags in its most serialized season yet -- mining thoughtful laughs from nostalgia, political correctness, and the trolling phenomenon.
